MIXXX, Contributor

I developed some moderate level features for MIXXX, an open-source DJ software. This was also my first contribution to opensource. As a contributor to the MIXXX project, I developed a context menu reset feature to reset the played counter (feature/bug), proposed and developed minute marker designs on a track’s waveform (feature/bug) and solved DAO issues for bulk file imports into the applications by applying transaction to the data imports, increased efficiency by a very huge factor (bug).

I am listed as a contributor on MIXXX project’s website here.
